  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely dice the <strong>brown&nbsp;onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of&nbsp;<strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>onion</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/603.-step--1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/603.-step--1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/603.-step--1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/603.-step--1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/603.-step--1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, wash then grate the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>directly into the pan with the onions</p>\r\n<p>Tear (or crumble) the <strong>chestnut&nbsp;</strong><strong>mushrooms</strong> into the pan</p>\r\n<p>Peel and grate the <strong>garlic</strong> directly into the pan</p>\r\n<p>Cook for 5 min or until everything is starting to soften&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Tip: crumbling the mushrooms adds texture and saves time!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/603.-step--2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/603.-step--2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/603.-step--2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/603.-step--2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/603.-step--2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, bring a large pot of <strong>salted boiled water</strong> to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>linguine</strong> and cook for 8-10 min or until cooked through but with a slight bite</p>\r\n<p>Once&nbsp;cooked, reserve approx.&nbsp;175ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span>&nbsp;<strong>starchy pasta water</strong>, then drain and return the pasta to the pot</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/603.-step--3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/603.-step--3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/603.-step--3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/603.-step--3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/603.-step--3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the<strong> beef mince</strong> to the softened vegetables and cook for a further 5 min or until the beef has browned&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Season with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> of both <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar&nbsp;</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/603.-step--4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/603.-step--4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/603.-step--4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/603.-step--4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/603.-step--4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile,&nbsp;stir the <strong>brown sauce </strong>and&nbsp;<strong>tomato paste </strong>into the reserved <strong>starchy pasta water</strong> with a large pinch of both&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong></p>\r\n<p>Stir to dissolve &ndash; this is your <strong>stock</strong></p>\r\n<p>Tip: pasta water is full of starch which helps your sauce stick to the linguine</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/603.-step--5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/603.-step--5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/603.-step--5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/603.-step--5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/603.-step--5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Stir the <strong>stock</strong> into the beef, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook until the sauce has a rag&ugrave;-like consistency (approx. 3-6 min)</p>\r\n<p>Once done, stir in the drained <strong>linguine</strong></p>\r\n<p>Taste for seasoning, adding <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> if needed</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/603.-step--6-x200.jpg",
